DE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ).  <br>
<br>
As for Yelinak, like someone said above, the only reason you'll need it is to turn in the head of King Tormax.  Not only that, but killing Tormax is a HUGE +Yelinak hit.  Supposedly 3 Tormaxes takes you from scowls to ally.  Basicly, you don't need yelinak till you can get Tormax's head, and once you can Yelinak faction is a breeze.  Btw, Tormax's guards also give Yelinak faction, however it's small so not worth killing them for faction alone. <p>~~
